    "introduction": "Through three characters who are reintegrated into everyday life after completing conscription, Viñas and Martínez Suárez built a complex social network in which university tensions, the decadence of industrial cinema and the venality of professional sport are represented, in addition to much of the daily life of Buenos Aires at the time. The film surprises for the precision of its shape and structure, but its validity surprises even more, more than sixty years after its realization. There is a record number of directors (or future directors) of Argentine cinema, both in front of and behind the camera.",
